Reasoning: The paper discusses the symbol grounding problem, which is a fundamental issue in natural language processing and artificial intelligence. The concept of reachable sets and algorithms to compute them are also introduced, which suggests a focus on computational methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.SD (Sound).
